Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem requires finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8\) are the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\).

For a continuous distribution, \(P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7\). The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to \(Y_7 \leq 27.3\) due to continuity. The probability \(P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\) is the probability that at least 7 of the 8 observations are \(\leq 27.3\).

Let \(B\) be the number of observations \(\leq 27.3\), so \(B \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7)\). Then:  
\[P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(B \geq 7) = P(B = 7) + P(B = 8).\]

Calculate each probability:  
\[P(B = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,\]  
\[P(B = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^8.\]

Compute \((0.7)^7\) and \((0.7)^8\):  
\[(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543,\]  
\[(0.7)^8 = 0.7 \times 0.0823543 = 0.05764801.\]

Then:  
\[P(B = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 8 \times 0.02470629 = 0.19765032,\]  
\[P(B = 8) = 0.05764801.\]

Sum the probabilities:  
\[P(B \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.\]

Rounding to four decimal places gives 0.2553. The value is reasonable as the inputs (e.g., 27.3) have three significant figures, and probabilities are typically reported to four decimal places.

