Solution: The sample mean \(\bar{X}\) for a random sample of size \(n = 12\) from a uniform distribution on \((0,1)\) has a mean \(\mu_{\bar{X}} = 0.5\) and a variance \(\sigma_{\bar{X}}^2 = \frac{1}{144}\), so the standard deviation is \(\sigma_{\bar{X}} = \frac{1}{12}\).

