- Upper bound: \(z_{\text{upper}} = \frac{\frac{2}{3} - 0.5}{1/12} = \frac{\frac{1}{6}}{1/12} = 2\)  

Thus, \(P(0.5 \leq \bar{X} \leq \frac{2}{3}) \approx P(0 \leq Z \leq 2)\), where \(Z\) is a standard normal variable.  
- \(P(Z \leq 2) \approx 0.97725\)  
- \(P(Z \leq 0) = 0.5\)  
- \(P(0 \leq Z \leq 2) = 0.97725 - 0.5 = 0.47725\)  

Rounded to three significant figures, the probability is 0.477.

