Solution: The problem requires finding the probability that the fourth white ball is drawn on the fourth draw when sampling with replacement from an urn with 10 red and 10 white balls. Since sampling is with replacement, the probability of drawing a white ball remains constant at \( \frac{10}{20} = 0.5 \) for each draw.

