  Given \(P(A \cup B') = 0.87\),  
  \[P(A' \cap B) = 1 - 0.87 = 0.13.\]

- Now, \(P(A') = P(A' \cap B) + P(A' \cap B')\), so  
  \[P(A') = 0.13 + 0.24 = 0.37.\]

- Therefore, \(P(A) = 1 - P(A') = 1 - 0.37 = 0.63\).

