- Energy per mole: \(E_{\text{mol}} = (6.626 \times 10^{-19}) \times (6.022 \times 10^{23}) = 3.990 \times 10^5 \, \text{J/mol} = 399 \, \text{kJ/mol}\) (rounded to three significant figures based on the wavelength input).

